  However, before full spawn had passed, I had to log to go to work.  I kept it on me for the time being.<br><br>Later in the day, I logged back on.  We were doing a raid on Velketor and I went.  Yasp needed just the Blue Throne to finish creating Plane of Mischief Mage leggings.  After teasing him a bit, I finally agreed to Mogur asking me to give the throne to Yasp.<br><br>Yasp and Mogur at the moment were trading.  Yasp was showing Mogur what cards he had.  I in the meantime was rapidly clicking on Yasp with the throne card wanting to trade it to him so I could go back to buffing myself with my okiels' boots over and over again as I usually do to pass the time.<br><br>As soon as Mogur and Yasp had finished, <br><br>The trade has been canceled.<br>The trade has been canceled.<br>The trade has been canceled.<br><br>Three times.  I checked my inventory.  Despite the Blue Throne being a tiny item, and me having more then one empty backpack, as well as an empty inventory slot, the throne was no longer there.  I had -never- hit the "Accept Trade" button.<br><br>I asked the guild if anyone had it.  Nobody did.  Both Mogur and Yasp denied having it.<br><br>Now, if you know Yasp, he's a bit of a dork, but honest.  He complains alot about the Mage epic, but he's shut up since he's finally finished.<br><br>Despite being an ass, Mogur is honest as well.  He's helped me finish -several- high end quests by generously giving me his own stuff to finish them.<br><br>I -know- it wasn't in my inventory, and I'm sure the GM would have later informed me it was still in my inventory.  Kinda hard to petition about something not being in your inventory when it's right there.  Anyways.<br><br>We (Yasp and Myself) petitioned.<br><br>Soon enough, Desilous (Our servers GM) responded.  I explained the situation up to that point, including what had happened earlier in the day as to how I aquired the card.<br><br>Desilous apparently had already been dealing with Yasp.  He informed Yasp that it had indeed been traded to someone, but he could not reveal to whom.  That made sense in and of itself to the both of us.  Yasp said so over the guild channel.<br><br>After a breif conversation in which I had explained what happened from my point of view, he told me he would have to look into it more, would get back to me and contact me when he found out what had happened.<br><br>About 30 seconds later he logged.<br><br>Several weeks went by.  Tired of waiting, I finally petitioned.<br><br>He told me the following.<br><br>1)  I had indeed traded it.<br>2)  He had "Talked to the person to whom I traded it to."<br>3)  He could not tell me to whom I traded it to.<br><br>After spending roughly half an hour asking why he couldn't inform me as to whom I had traded it to, he logged without explanation.<br><br>Tonight I petitioned again.<br><br>After half an hour, and several guildmates co-petitioning along with me, and explaining that it was -ridiculous- that I shouldn't be allowed to know where something from -my- inventory had gone, he "recieved permission" to tell me to whom I traded it.  He said I gave it to Mogur.<br><br>Before he finally broke down however, the following occured.<br><br>1)  He accused Yasp of having it (Yasp said as such in the guild channel).  Yasp denied having it at any point.  We all know that neither Yasp, nor Mogur, nor I have it, nor had it at any point after the defunct trade.<br><br>2)  He informs me that I did indeed trade it to someone.  It is the only way it could have gotten to another persons inventory.<br><br>3)  He informs me that he contacted the person to whom I had traded it.<br><br>4)  He informs me that he asked for the throne back from whom I gave it to.<br><br>This is where it gets fun.  He says, and I quote.  Hell, I'll bust an image with some of the tells on it.<br><br><img src="http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/liar.gif"><br><br>Now, as you can see, Desilous proves to be an idiot here.  Anyone can see that if I had traded it to someone, and that person claims to have looted it, and the logs show I traded it to someone...gee, put 2 and 2 together folks, the person I accidentally gave it to through some bug is a liar.  Right?<br><br>Well, this is where it gets interesting.  I talked to Mogur some.<br><br>This is what he had to say to me.  Now remember, Mogur has given me in excess of 70K in items of value to help me finish quests.<br><br>Mogur talked to Desilous aparently earlier about what had happened.  Mogur at -no- point was -ever- asked by Desilous to give it back.  He merely explained that he had looted it and given it to me.  Anyone who has had dealings with Mogur has probably found him crude and an asshole to boot, but honest.  Mogur does not have it.  He just checked his inventory again now.  He has the other three colored thrones, but not the blue throne.<br><br>Someone here is lying.  And I, as well as all of you I'm sure, are inclined to believe Mogur and I in this, rather then Desilous who had kept going back on himself, and had accused Yasp of having it and saying something completely different to me.<br><br>Fun huh?  We have a corrupt GM.  Yay!<br><br> <p><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=24873><img src=http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/sexy.gif></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uyasp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yasp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/7/01 8:16:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=440.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> so true</span><hr size=1> Honestly this guy is a piece of work.  <br><br>1. Accused me of having it the day of the petition. However the next time 