the hell would he do with a blue card? He follows the rules set forth for him like all members of the Customer Service team...not to screw over the player but to help the player when they can while not jeopardizing the other players. The only people who have something to gain are yourself and possibly the people you traded to.<br><br>Fourth, GMs are required as part of their job to have an active account and play at least on a daily basis to understand the player. I am sure he has undergone similar circumstances and rather than being able to summon up the items has dealt with a GM saying no to him in the past. Keep in mind they probably understand what you are going through.<br><br>And finally, as part of the playing agreement, you are supposed to understand that there are 8 zones listed as CS Restricted Zones. These zones include Plane of Fear, Plane of Hate, Plane of Air, Veeshan's Peak, Plane of Growth, Plane of Mischief, Temple of Veeshan, Sleeper's Tomb. A CS restricted zone means that items lost from these zones are completely off limits to Apprentice Guides and only Guides+ are allowed to enter with their Server GM's permission. Furthermore, the Server GM is encouraged to simply say &quot;sorry&quot; and end any and all investigations regarding items, mobs, CRs, etc. in these zones because their difficulty and integrety must remain intact. The fact that he investigated the issue was more than he had to, and then now you don't like his ruling you are supposed to e-mail eqmail@station.sony.com to speak to his supervisor, not act like a little 2 year old and piss and moan behind his back.<br><br>Ultimately I am getting pretty tired of people pissing and moaning about guides, etc. Sure, they are never around because so many quit because the players are such pains in the ass. That is why I quit, it wasn't fun. Frankly every member of the customer service team is paid FAR LESS than the work they put out (as a guide I got $9.95 / 24 hours / month) ...that comes from their love of the game and their love of the player base. Instead of being stupid you have options such as overruling a guide's verdict by going to their supervisor instead of acting like a disgruntled child, and maybe the next time a guide says no to you, you can respect that because they are doing their job..and would love to help you if they could. <p><img src="http://eagle2.american.edu/~ch4890a/kelsig.jpg"><br><center><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/userinfo.html?char=126095">----Profile----</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ussfourgoku.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ssfourgoku</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/7/01 8:28:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=440.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: so true</span><hr size=1> hehhehe. hes nice to me. i get anythign i want. so yes its a GM overpowering his ability but hey, some people cant controll themselves. like my friend tom and ben who have to talk about my mom to make a point, go figure.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utheperfectflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThePerfectFlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/7/01 8:45:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=440.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/jolly.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: so true</span><hr size=1> No offense Kelraz, but through the entire process, he treated myself an others like crap.  He lied to myself and Ya